            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.45"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">45</fw>
                <fw type="authorial"></fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        April 28-71
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Listening to you was like food or drink after a long hard March.</p> 
                <p>I am trying to find your writings. The library is getting one book, the one you mentioned on T.V.</p>
                <p>You must have earlier writing's</p>
                <p>I am a mystic, and much interested in spiritual matters.</p> 
                <p>I know the real meaning of mysticism, as I know you do.</p> 
                <p>I'd love to know more from one much wiser than I.</p> 
                <p>Life is a lonely waiting to find spiritual relatives &#8212; they are <unclear/> among the young Hippies so called 
                
                <pb/>

                
                today, but who are really aware as you declared on T.V.</p> 
                <p>I am in early sixtie's and became aware nearly 18 years ago, after much pondering.</p> 
                <p>I read the writings of Glena Clark of MacAlester College in Minnesota.</p> 
                <p>I also read Evelyn Underhill and Saint Theresa:</p> 
                <p>I read the religions, each one, <unclear>before</unclear> I turned to the Mystics.</p> 
                <p>If its possible to answer, tell me about your poems, where I can get them, and all your books. I recognize you as a great Soul. Your views on animal killing were also mine.</p> 
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>My dearest wishes,</salute> 
                    <signed>Norma Conlin</signed> 
                </closer>
            </div1>
            
